# Getting started

The first time you use the Sirv REST API, create an API client, then connect to Sirv. Once connected, you can use over 30 API methods.

# API client

To use the Sirv REST API, create an API client from the <a href="https://my.sirv.com/#/account/settings" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Settings page of your Sirv account</a>:

![Create API Client](https://sirv.sirv.com/website/screenshots/sirv-api-client-create.png?profile=screenshots-grey-border)

Once created, you'll see your Client ID and Client Secret:

![API Client Credentials](https://sirv.sirv.com/website/screenshots/sirv-api-client-list.png?profile=screenshots-grey-border)

# Connect to Sirv API

Each API call must be authenticated with a bearer token (JSON Web Token).
You can get a token with a POST request. Use the token with the Sirv REST API methods listed below.
When the token expires (see the expiresIn field, in seconds), you should request a new token.

